## 4. Design System Enforcement

**Before writing or modifying ANY UI code**, you MUST follow these rules:

### The Three Laws of Color
1. **Teal for actions** — every CTA, toggle, active state, tier badge, interactive highlight
2. **Blue for data** — clicks, sessions, impressions, info badges, progress bars (read-only, never actionable)
3. **Purple for admin AI only** — `AdminChat.tsx` and `SeoAudit.tsx` "Flag for Client". **Never in client-facing views.**

### Color Decision Quick Reference
```
Button / CTA / toggle?      → Teal (from-teal-600 to-emerald-600)
Data metric?                 → Blue (text-blue-400, bg-blue-500/10)
Admin AI feature?            → Purple (purple-400/purple-600)
Score (health/perf)?         → scoreColor() from constants.ts
Status badge?                → green (success), amber (warning), red (error), orange (changes requested), blue (info/review), teal (client requested)
Tier badge (client)?         → Teal (all tiers) or zinc (free)
```

### Forbidden
- **Never** use `violet`, `indigo`, or introduce new hue families without explicit user approval
- **Never** hand-roll card markup — use `<SectionCard>`
- **Never** hand-roll stat displays — use `<StatCard>` or `<CompactStatBar>`
- **Never** hard-code score colors — use `scoreColor()` / `scoreColorClass()` from `ui/constants.ts`
- **Never** use purple in any client-facing component

### UI Primitives (always use before hand-rolling)

| Primitive | Import from | Use for |
|-----------|------------|---------|
| `SectionCard` | `./ui` | Any card container |
| `StatCard` / `CompactStatBar` | `./ui` | Metric displays |
| `PageHeader` | `./ui` | Page/tab header with title + actions |
| `MetricRing` / `MetricRingSvg` | `./ui` | Score rings |
| `Badge` | `./ui` | Status/category pills (9 colors) |
| `TabBar` | `./ui` | Sub-navigation tabs |
| `DateRangeSelector` | `./ui` | Segmented date pickers |
| `DataList` | `./ui` | Ranked list displays |
| `EmptyState` | `./ui` | Empty data placeholders |
| `TierGate` / `TierBadge` | `./ui` | Tier lock overlay + badge |
